Double Lemon Cheesecake Bars
  --Philadelphia Cream Cheese

52 vanilla wafers, finely crushed (~2 c)
3 tbsp butter, melted
4 eggs, divided
4x8z pkg cream cheese, softened
1 3/4 c sugar, divided
3 tbsp flour
1 tbsp zest + 1/3 c juice from 2 lemons, divided
1/2 tsp vanilla
2 tbsp cornstarch
1/2 c water

Heat oven to 325F. Line 13x9" pan with foil, making an overhang. Mix crumbs and butter until blended; press onto bottom of prepared pan. Bake 10 min. Separate 1 egg, refrigerate yolk until ready to use. Beat cream cheese, 1 c sugar, flour, lemon zest, 2 tbsp lemon juice, and vanilla in large bowl until blended. Add egg white and remaning eggs, 1 at a time, mixing on low speed after each, until just blended. Pour over crust. Bake 40 min, or until center is almost set. Cool 1 hr; refrigerate 4 hrs. Mix cornstarch and remaining sugar in medium saucepan, gradually stir in water and remaining lemon juice until blended. Bring just to a boil on medium heat, stirring constantly. Cook until clear and thickend. Lightly beat reserved egg yolk in small bowl with a fork until blended. Stir in 2 tbsp of cornstarch mixture into yolk, then combine resulting in pan with remaining cornstarch mixture (temper). Cook 1 min or until thickened, stirring constantly. Cool slightly. Spoon lemon glaze over cheesecake. Refrigerate 1 hr or until firm. Use foil to lift out and cut bars. Serve. Makes 16.
